HEADWORD: Setigerous
<hw>Se*tig"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Seta</ets>
+ <ets>-gerous</ets>.]</ety> <def>Covered with bristles; having or
bearing a seta or setae; setiferous; <as>as, <ex>setigerous</ex> glands;
a <ex>setigerous</ex> segment of an annelid</as>; specifically
<fld>(Bot.)</fld>, tipped with a bristle.</def>⟦br⟧
